text: ['3.1.7  Import licensing, prohibitions and other restrictions', '3.34.  According  to  the  customs  authorities,  Chad  does  not  apply  import  prohibitions  except for those  provided  in  connection  with  environmental  protection,  and  those  arising  from its international commitments (Table 3.3). According to the authorities, no quantitative restriction is  currently  in  force.  Import  and  export  licensing  regimes  were  abolished  in  1995,  except  for sulphur and other explosives.
